00:00:06.890 --> 00:00:11.299
There are new stars emerging from the British
Airgun Championships at Bisley.

00:00:11.299 --> 00:00:16.640
Berkshire teenager Charlotte Huddart won two
gold medals and a championship silver medal.

00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:21.330
She goes to Germany next to compete against
teams from South Africa and Denmark. Meanwhile,

00:00:21.330 --> 00:00:25.960
three members of Bideford Target Shooting
Club in Devon came home with medals. Between

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:31.119
them, Michael Coombs, Clive Magson and Alex
Raymon won four golds, one silver and a bronze

00:00:31.119 --> 00:00:36.620
The organisation representing Scottish solicitors
believes that the new proposed legislation

00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:40.380
on airguns will make them untraceable.

00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:44.020
The SNP has introduced its bill requiring
anyone who owns an air pistol or rifle to

00:00:44.020 --> 00:00:48.720
apply for a certificate similar to a shotgun
certificate but without requiring the guns

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:53.590
to be listed. Campaigners claim the proposals
are draconian and they point out that offences

00:00:53.590 --> 00:01:03.300
involving air weapons have fallen by 75% from
683 to 171 by 2013, the lowest since records

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:04.300
began.

00:01:04.300 --> 00:01:08.390
